1. **`packages/ai/src/articleService.ts`** — AI service with `generateArticleQuestions()` that accepts article content, title, topic, and question count, returns IELTS-style questions (multiple-choice, true-false, short-answer, gap-fill, matching) with difficulty/bandScore estimates. Uses user's own AI API key from settings.

2. **`packages/ai/src/index.ts`** — Exports `generateArticleQuestions`, `articleQuestionSchema`, `ArticleQuestion`, `ArticleQuestionSet`.

3. **`apps/extension/src/storage/articleStore.ts`** — IndexedDB store for articles: schema (`ExtensionArticleEntry`) with title, URL, content, selected paragraph, topic, tags, reading practice flag, AI questions array. CRUD operations + query methods (`getArticlesByTopic`, `getReadingPracticeArticles`, `getArticleStats`). DB version bumped to 3.

4. **`apps/extension/src/popup/components/ArticleCollector.tsx`** — Popup UI component with:
   - Auto-populates title/URL/selected text from current page
   - Full article content + selected paragraph fields
   - IELTS topic dropdown (predefined topics), difficulty selector, tags, note
   - "Mark as Reading practice" checkbox
   - **AI question generation** — button generates 3-5 IELTS questions from content, preview panel shows questions with type/difficulty badges, options, correct answer, and explanation
   - Save to IndexedDB, updates daily progress counter

5. **`apps/extension/src/popup/App.tsx`** — Added `ArticleCollector` import + `articleCollector` view routing, replaced old "Save Current Page" button with "📰 Save Article" action.

Both packages (`packages/ai` and `apps/extension`) compile clean with `tsc --noEmit`. No test files exist for the extension yet.
